# Cloudflare Pages _redirects. Copied verbatim from `frontend/public/` into
# `dist/` at build time by Vite's static-asset pass. First match wins.
#
# Since the build emits a top-level dist/404.html (see scripts/prerender.ts),
# Pages no longer SPA-falls-back unmatched paths to the index shell with 200.
# Any path with no static file and no rule here is served 404.html with a 404
# status — which fixes the missing-/assets/*.js MIME violation but means every
# non-prerendered route must be handled explicitly below, before the implicit
# 404 fallback.
#
# Trailing-slash → non-trailing canonical. The build emits `dist/<slug>.html`
# (file, not directory) for every indexable route, so Pages serves `/<slug>`
# with 200 directly. Anyone who lands on `/<slug>/` — old inbound links,
# third-party share tools that auto-append `/` — gets a 308 to the canonical
# no-trailing form. Search Console previously flagged the (old) `/<slug>` →
# `/<slug>/` 308 chain as "page avec redirection", suppressing the indexable URL.
#
# 308 (not 301) preserves the request method on rewrite; matches the
# default Cloudflare Pages emits for the inverse rule.

/grille/             /grille             308
/grilles/            /grilles            308
/aide/               /aide               308
/mentions-legales/   /mentions-legales   308
/confidentialite/    /confidentialite    308
/privacy/            /privacy            308
/compte/             /compte             308

# Legacy survey aliases. The /sondage surface was renamed to /contribuer;
# these were client-side beforeLoad redirects but the 404.html change turns
# off the SPA fallback they relied on, so they're now server-side 308s.
# Trailing-slash variants land directly on the canonical /contribuer form.
/sondage/pairs/      /contribuer/pairs   308
/sondage/pairs       /contribuer/pairs   308
/sondage/            /contribuer         308
/sondage             /contribuer         308

# Client-only dynamic routes. No prerendered file exists, so rewrite to the
# shell with 200 (NOT a redirect) — a multiplayer share link or a refresh on
# a lobby must resolve the param client-side, never 404 or bounce to home.
/lobby/*             /index.html         200
/join/*              /index.html         200
